  "analysis": "I have successfully navigated to /home/user and examined the diagnostics.ini configuration file. The file appears to be encoded in ISO-8859-1 as warned, containing special characters in the copyright header. I have extracted the required parameters: NET_IFACE=lo and PING_HOST=127.0.0.1. Next I need to collect network interface data and system information to populate the JSON output file.",
  "plan": "1. Collect current UTC timestamp in ISO-8601 format. 2. Get network interface configuration for 'lo' including name, primary IP, and MTU. 3. Determine default gateway with lowest metric. 4. Count established TCP connections. 5. Calculate ping jitter to 127.0.0.1. 6. Assemble all data into the required JSON structure. 7. Generate the network_data.json file with UTF-16LE encoding and BOM.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "date -u +\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\"\n",
